# Use case map canvas (must stay in sync)

Whenever you **finish a change** that alters **player-visible behaviour or navigation** — new or removed actions, tabs, buttons, voyage rules, intel flows, save fields the UI depends on, or similar — update the living map:

`canvases/harbours-use-case-map.canvas.tsx`  
(resolved path: `~/.cursor/projects/Users-ari-lahti-HarboursOfPower/canvases/harbours-use-case-map.canvas.tsx`)

## Files that commonly require a canvas pass

Touch any of these (or add a new UI entry point tied to `GameState`) and reconcile the canvas **in the same change** when behaviour or copy shipped to the player changes:

- `ui/main.gd` (city places, trade, voyage, admin, signals)
- `autoload/game_state.gd` when it adds/changes **player-invokable** APIs used by UI or new **signals** the UI should surface
- `main.tscn` or other primary UI scenes if they add/remove controls that change flows
- `data/world.json`, `data/goods.json`, `data/ships.json` when the change **changes what the player can do** (e.g. new good category with market row, new port capability like mint/tolls), not for pure balance tweaks that do not change affordances

## What to update

- **Use case catalogue** — add/remove/rename rows; keep IDs stable unless the feature is renamed on purpose.
- **Player states / macro loop / surfaces** — if docked vs at sea, tabs, or header semantics change.
- **UI ↔ simulation wiring** — new or removed `GameState` signals or main-scene subscriptions.
- **Cross-links** — if economy tick docs moved, adjust the pointer to `harbours-economy-rules.canvas.tsx`.

## Skip only when

- Refactor with **identical** player-visible behaviour and navigation, **or**
- Changes confined to assets, internal-only sim, or tests with no UI or player contract change.

## Relation to other rules

- **Economy rules canvas** — still update that canvas when **documented economy / twin behaviour** changes (`update-economy-rules-canvas.mdc`). This use-case canvas is **flow and UI oriented**; both may need edits for one feature.
- **Post-change sim** — unchanged; run the sim when that rule applies regardless of this doc.
